    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>We surveyed 10,024 Australians regarding COVID-19 vaccine willingness. Overall, 59.9% indicated yes, 13.9% no and 26.3% unsure/don\u2019t know. Vaccine willingness was higher in males, and increased with increasing education and socioeconomic advantage. Results contrast with earlier, smaller Australian surveys regarding vaccination willingness and confirm the need for targeted vaccination information.</jats:p>",
